cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PL 

This paper deals with the problem of implementing atomic read/write objects in distributed computing systems, which is a core topic in the field of Distributed Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the efficiency of algorithms in terms of communication exchanges, which is a key aspect of Distributed Systems (cs.DS). The paper presents new algorithms for read operations that improve on prior works, which is a contribution to the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also rigorously argues the correctness of the algorithms, which is a common theme in the field of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with the implementation of algorithms, which is a topic in Programming Languages (cs.PL).
